parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake lines due to corrosion can cause sudden and unexpected loss of brake function, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal travels to the floor
excessive pedal travel
extended stopping distance
brake fluid leaking from beneath the vehicle
corrosion visible on brake lines
brake lines rupture
and brake calipers lock up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake calipers due to corrosion can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake calipers lock up
brake fluid leaking from beneath the vehicle
corrosion visible on brake calipers
and brake lines rupture.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case oil pump can cause oil leaks, leading to premature wear on the transfer case and related components, which can result in costly repairs and potentially leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil leak from the tail housing of the transfer case
repeated seal failures
oil pump wearing a hole through the tail shaft housing from the inside out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the limited slip differential can cause uneven tire wear, reduced traction, and loss of control, especially during sharp turns, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Rear tires do not have limited slip
rear end behaves like a solid axle
excessive wear and tear on tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving or at a stop
the engine stalls without any warning lights or trouble codes
the headlights or interior lights dim or flicker
the engine stalls intermittently over a long period of time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of brake lines can cause sudden brake failure, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake lines rupture
corrosion visible on brake lines
brake fluid leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic behavior of the fuel gauge can lead to unexpected fuel depletion, causing drivers to become stranded, potentially in hazardous situations, and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The fuel gauge suddenly drops to empty or fluctuates erratically
providing inaccurate fuel level readings
and may cause the vehicle to run out of fuel without warning.
